# 📈 Stock Price Forecasting with EMA and LSTM

This repository presents an end-to-end stock price forecasting project that combines **Exploratory Data Analysis (EDA)**, **Technical Analysis**, and **Deep Learning** to predict the closing price of **Société Générale (GLE.PA)** stock.

The study uses daily historical market data covering the period **2000–2025**. Two forecasting approaches are implemented and compared:

* **Exponential Moving Average (EMA)** for short-term trend forecasting.
* **Long Short-Term Memory (LSTM)**, a deep learning architecture designed to capture temporal dependencies in financial time series.

The project includes data preprocessing, exploratory analysis, technical visualization, model development, performance evaluation, and prediction of stock closing prices.

## Key Features

* 📊 Exploratory Data Analysis (EDA)
* 📈 Technical Analysis of historical stock prices
* 🔄 Exponential Moving Average (EMA) forecasting
* 🤖 Deep Learning with LSTM neural networks
* 📉 Stock price prediction and model evaluation
* 📏 Performance assessment using Mean Squared Error (MSE)

## Results

The EMA model provides effective short-term trend estimation, while the LSTM model successfully captures both short- and long-term price dynamics. Model performance is evaluated using **Mean Squared Error (MSE)**, demonstrating satisfactory predictive capability on the test data.
